Jeff Wicks, News24 WATCH: Demonstrators in Zandspruit, Johannesburg enter their fourth day of action over cut electricity.WATCH Durban - The N2 in the vicinity of Mandini on the KZN North Coast has been closed to traffic after protestors erected burning barricades on Tuesday morning.  Road Traffic Inspectorate spokesperson Zinhle Mngomezulu said that the freeway had been closed in both directions.  She described the incident as a “public protest”.  “They have closed the road and they are burning tyres. That is all we know at this point.” IPSS Security spokesperson Dylan Meyrick had earlier reported that both the N2 and the R102, the main arterial routes to Zululand, had been blockaded.  This is a developing story.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  